"The 2004 CES is a fantastic world-class event; any one doing anything of significance in relation to consumer electronics should be here!"
<p>
Michael Ahn, president and CEO, LG Electronics USA Inc., Englewood Cliffs, NJ 
"The 2004 CES represented the launch of LG-branded consumer electronics in the USA.  The show provided an excellent venue to highlight our digital displays and other products while establishing a strong brand recognition.  Most importantly, meeting with key customers was a major emphasis at CES.  We plan to double our booth space for 2005."
<p>
Sean Fields, president, A/V Entertainment, Laguna Niguel, CA 
"I have experienced an increase of system integrator attendance at the 2004 International CES.  I believe this is due to the latest addition of beneficial education programs for our industry.  I am also delighted to see more international attendance from our niche.  This year is the best CES I have ever attended."
<p>
Bob Struble, president and CEO, iBiquity Digital Corp., Columbia, MD 
"The 2004 CES was everything we could have hoped for to mark the consumer launch of HD radio.  All our key target constituents were here in force - CE manufacturers, retailers, press and media, government officials, automakers, semiconductor manufacturers - and our schedule was full.  There is no other single even which could provide us so much value."
<p>	
Michael O'Hara, executive vice president, consumer products, marketing and sales, Thomson, Indianapolis, IN
